        <div id="ember580" class="ember-view"><h2 id="1introduction">1. Introduction</h2>
        <p>This User Agreement and all policies and additional terms posted on and in our platform, which is comprised of our websites, services, and/or applications mobile or otherwise (together, "NeoScaffold"), set out the terms on which NeoScaffold Inc. (referred to in this policy as "NeoScaffold", "we", "us") offers you access to and use of NeoScaffold. All policies and additional terms posted on and in NeoScaffold are incorporated into this User Agreement. If we update it, we will revise the date, place notices on NeoScaffold if changes are material, and/or obtain your consent as required by law. You agree to comply with all of the terms of this User Agreement when accessing or using NeoScaffold.</p>
        <h2 id="2aboutneoscaffold">2. About NeoScaffold</h2>
        <p>NeoScaffold is an application that facilitates workflow creation and management. Users can design, implement, and optimize various business processes and workflows. NeoScaffold provides tools and guidance for creating, editing, and managing workflows, but the actual implementation and use of these workflows are the responsibility of the users. NeoScaffold cannot guarantee and has no control over: </p>
        <ul>
        <li>the efficiency or effectiveness of user-created workflows; </li>
        <li>the accuracy or completeness of user-input data or workflow designs; </li>
        <li>users' proper implementation of the workflows they create; </li>
        <li>users' ability to manage or optimize their workflows, or the outcomes of implementing these workflows.</li>
        </ul>
        <h2 id="3usingneoscaffold">3. Using NeoScaffold</h2>
        <p>When you use or access NeoScaffold you will not:</p>
        <ul>
        <li>use NeoScaffold for any purpose other than creating, managing, or optimizing workflows;</li>
        <li>breach or circumvent any laws, third-party rights, or our policies;</li>
        <li>use our services if you are not able to form legally binding contracts (for example, if you are under 18 years of age), or are temporarily or permanently suspended from using NeoScaffold;</li>
        <li>create workflows that violate any applicable laws, regulations, or ethical standards;</li>
        <li>interfere with workflows or content that you are not directly involved with;</li>
        <li>post or create false, inaccurate, misleading, deceptive, defamatory, or libelous content;</li>
        <li>undermine or manipulate our feedback and rating systems;</li>
        <li>impersonate another individual or organization, or misrepresent your affiliation with any individual or organization;</li>
        <li>distribute, use, or create content, software, or media that is harmful to NeoScaffold, its affiliates, or its users;</li>
        <li>use, export, reverse-engineer, or manipulate any part of NeoScaffold in a way that violates our terms;</li>
        <li>collect or harvest information about users or content posted to NeoScaffold by any automated means;</li>
